<!DOCTYPE html>

html
    head
        meta(charset="utf-8" )
        title

    body 
        div Search can be performed on CustomerId, FirstName, LastName and City for sample purpose. To achieve this a view on customers db called composite which create indexes on id, firstname,lastname and city using emit<br/>
        |implementation details can be found in customers.js in routes folder
        
        br

        form(action="/customers/search" method="get")
            label Type Search
            input(name="searchTerm" type="text")
            button Search
        br
        form(action="/customers/create" method="get")            
            button Create Customer
         br
       table(width="100%" border="1" align="center" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;")          
            thead
                tr
                    td( colspan="4" style="padding:5px;text-align:center;") Customer Id
                    td( colspan="4" style="padding:5px;text-align:center;") First Name
                    td( colspan="4" style="padding:5px;text-align:center;") Last Name
                    td( colspan="4" style="padding:5px;text-align:center;") AddressLine 1
                    td( colspan="4" style="padding:5px;text-align:center;") AddressLine 2
                    td( colspan="4" style="padding:5px;text-align:center;") City
                    td( colspan="4" style="padding:5px;text-align:center;") State
                    td( colspan="4" style="padding:5px;text-align:center;") Country
                      
             tbody
                

                    each item in CustomerList
                        tr
                            td( colspan="4" style="padding:5px;text-align:center;")= item.doc._id
                            td( colspan="4" style="padding:5px;text-align:center;")= item.doc.FirstName
                            td( colspan="4" style="padding:5px;text-align:center;")= item.doc.LastName
                            td( colspan="4" style="padding:5px;text-align:center;")= item.doc.Address.AddressLine1
                            td( colspan="4" style="padding:5px;text-align:center;")= item.doc.Address.AddressLine2
                            td( colspan="4" style="padding:5px;text-align:center;")= item.doc.Address.City
                            td( colspan="4" style="padding:5px;text-align:center;")= item.doc.Address.State
                            td( colspan="4" style="padding:5px;text-align:center;")= item.doc.Address.Country
            
                            
                            
